        Chart Review 01/09/2023

        Yes. That is all. Ok, I'll add to this review.

        You may know by now that I keep banging my head against a wall with self-doubt, desperately praying that the lady known universally as "Olivia Rodrigo", can get to the top again. Now it's happened, and yet I feel kinda guilty. Not her fault, obviously, getting a third chart-topper is bound to get the fanbase rocking, especially 'cause it's taken 9 flippin' weeks to get there. It's just... it feels a little manipulated, y'know?

        Doja Cat will probably be disappointed thatPaint The Town Redcouldn't take advantage of her dominance in the streaming, the highlight being her valiant assault on the Spotify charts to get to the top, the first song since Sprinter happened to get to the summit. That, combined with O-Rod being a somewhat distant loser on that front, should've meant that young Doje could get her 1st best-seller, right? RIGHT!?

        wrong.

        Instead, thanks to CDs or whatever,vampireis No.1, and I am perfectly fine with it. All of it bodes well for when GUTS hits the stores next Friday, so prepare your ears. I know I will.

        In other news, Dua Lipa's been shafted by the rules again. Last week's number one suddenly slips to 15 this week, in an act last seen when Lewis Capaldi fixed his way to the top. Except this has nothing to do with physical copies, and more to do with the fact thatACRexists. Which , I'm sure. Becky Hill keeps climbing, and if you heard her at Reading festival, you may have noted that she wants this song at No.5. She couldn't even get that right, the lazy sausage. (just kidding.)

        Als making inrads, but less excitingly, is cass, the DJ yu've never heard f, and yet has a Top 10 hit t his name. I fficially nw hate his hit. Blame D-Block Eurpe, alright? I didn't thinkPradawas that huge either, but here we are. And I'm nt very happy. NT HAPPY. I will als replace any "o"s with ""s whever i talk abut this sng. Deal with it, lame-'s.

        Right, new entries now, and Miley Cyrus will never leave the chart. Ever. She's still gonna be here when the sun swallows the Earth and we all die a horrible death. But for now, here's limp predictable balladUsed To Be Youngto make you feel better. It will certainly make you feel more alive than I am talking about this one. And no, this isn't because my mum likes it. Honest.

        As for the others, Selena Gomez hasn't had a thrilling return to the music industry, mainly because, erm... NOBODY WANTS HER TO. Not after the horrific 26 weeks I had to endure ofCalm Downbeing in the Top 10 because of her influence. It was mindnumbing. Thankfully,Single Soonis way better than that travesty, but only turns out to be blindingly average. Just like most of her catalogue. ;) (now is the time to abuse me in the comments, fellow users)

        And then there's Burna Boy. Everyone loves him. You do, I do, Ed Sheeran does. EVERYONE likes Burna Boy, which doesn't acocunt for the fact his chart history hasn't been spectacular in recent times. Hopefully his new No.1 album can address these difficulties, and with it comes 2 Top 40 songs to smear their way into your affections,Cheat On Me, which has Dave on it, so you know it's gonna be good, andCity Boys, which isn't good. But well done or whatever. I prefer Big 7 anyway.

        I'm gonna cut this review short because I'm STILL. ON. HOLIDAY. GOODNIGHT.


        (P.S. When watching a Top of the Pops re-run from 1986 earlier today, it feels honorable to compareBarbie Worldby Nicki Minaj and Ice Spice, withHoliday Rapby MC Miker G and Daddy Sven. And yes, you need to listen to that song. It's a statement. It's a privilege. It definitely isn't Haven caravan park fluff you drink your sorrows away to. And it also sampled an iconic song.)
